    {\displaystyle (B_{k+1},bit(C_{k},A_{k+1}),D)=M(B_{k},bit(C_{k},A_{k}))}
  . Since M has a finite domain, this can be replaced by a first-order quantifier-free arithmetic formula. The exact formula obviously depends on M.

  
    
      
        
